On (0, 1]: Use |1 - cos(st)| ≤ (st)²/2 ≤ t²s²/2, so |(1 - cos(st)) / s^{3/2}| ≤ t² * s^{1/2} / 2. The function s ↦ s^{1/2} is integrable on (0, 1] since 1/2 > -1. Use integrableOn_Ioc_rpow or direct computation.

